    "enDesc": "Chaim of Volozhin’s major work is the Nefesh HaChayim (\"Living Soul\"). Contrary to popular belief, ‎it does not deal solely with complex understandings of the nature of God, but also with secrets of ‎prayer and the importance of Torah, the purpose being \"to implant the fear of God, Torah, and ‎pure worship into the hearts of the upright who are seeking the ways of God\". It presents a clear ‎and orderly kabbalistic Weltanschauung that addresses many of the same issues as ‎the Hasidic texts of the day.‎",
    "enShortDesc": "Major 19th-century work of Rav Chaim of Volozhin on human purpose, God, Torah study, and prayer, incorporating kabbalistic elements.",
    "heShortDesc": "חיבורו המונומנטלי של הרב חיים מוולוז'ין, בן המאה ה-19, העוסק במטרת החיים, באלוהות, בלימוד תורה ובתפילה ומשלב אלמנטים קבליים.",
    "pubDate": "1824",
    "compDate": "1800",
    "compPlace": "Valozhyn",
    "pubPlace": "Vilnius/Grodno",
